Lewis parks his W13 in the garage and retires from the Grand Prix.

George peels into the pit lane and moves onto a fresh set of Mediums. Another strong stop, but he falls behind VER.
Fastest driver on track right now? Lewis Hamilton 👀
Some EPIC defensive driving from George but he can't hold LEC back any longer! Let's keep pushing though, GR 💪

Lap 20: Lewis pits for a fresh set of Mediums and exits the pits P7 - good stop, Team 👏

Lap 17: “Box Box”

George pits for Medium tyres and emerges P6 just ahead of ALO

Lap 15: SAI has turned up the pace and closed the gap to George.

Currently 1.3s between P1 and P2 👀
Lap 12: Lovely move, Lewis!! 👏👏👏 Moves to the inside of NOR into Turn1 and is up to P4!

Lap 10: Lewis now all over the back of NOR but he has VER closing in behind him.

Currently running in P5 💪

Lap 6: George holding the gap fairly stable to SAI behind, at just over 2s

Meanwhile Lewis is latched onto the gearbox of NOR’s McLaren in the fight for P4
Lap 3: Back to green flag racing and George maintains the lead, with a good jump on the Ferraris 👊
Lovely starts, boys 👌
Lap 2: VSC deployed, for debris at Turn 2 ⚠️

Text: The Turn 3 Switchback 👌
LAP 62: Awesome job, George! He overtakes OCO and is into P4! 👏
LAP 60: The race goes back to green flag running with Lewis P3 and George P5!
LAP 58: VSC deployed after SAI stops at the side of the track with an issue.

LAP 52: "Box, box."

Lewis pits for the Medium tyre. Maximum attack to the end 🔥🔥🔥
LAP 45: Lovely, lovely stuff George! Two overtakes in one lap! He's now up to P8 💪
📸🔥 https://t.co/NA8ZP9CQSa
LAP 41: George pits for another set of Hard tyres and a front wing adjust - it's a lovely 2.7s stop 👌
Lovely move, LH! 👏 He quickly dispatches of OCO and is now back up to P4

LAP 29: "Box, box"

Lewis stops for the Hard tyre and emerges in P6 behind OCO
LAP 28: George making solid progress on the Hard tyre, still struggling with some understeer but steadily making up places - currently P11 https://t.co/QfS5k3AeXa
It’s hammer time 🔨 Lewis in clear air and matching the pace of the Ferraris 👊 https://t.co/9LkuKbRYP6
LAP 15: And another one! Lewis dives down the inside of MAG at Turn 4 and into P4 on the road 🦈
LAP 14: Lewis gets the undercut on MSC through the exit of Turn 6 and dives down the inside at Turn 7! 👏👏
What an overtake, Lewis!!!!
LAP 11: George has been given a five-second time penalty for the lap one collision.
LAP 9: George is suffering from that front wing damage but holding onto P4, with a train of cars behind, including Lewis, who is right behind MSC
Lewis runs slightly wide and onto the kerb at Turn 1, which drops him behind MSC and into P8
Suspension is okay, George is told, but he’s lost the left front end plate and reports understeer

And it’s LIGHTS OUT for the #AustrianGP!

Text: Into the final minutes at Monaco. https://t.co/Bdil4pcUFH

15 minutes left on the race clock. ⏰

George running in fifth, managing some graining on his Medium tyres. https://t.co/exQtfCgr4h
It’s this close. 🤏 https://t.co/o3d1s7Gz5j

George's pace looking nice here. Lapping just a few tenths shy of the front four. 👊

Lewis is stuck behind Fernando - who's lapping three seconds off the pace.

LH glued to the gearbox of the Alpine. Waiting for a chance to try and snatch P7.
One for all the geeks. Lewis has switched back to his 💛 and 💜 during the red flag.

Cars head back on track behind the Safety Car. This race will now go to the two hour limit. 

George and Lewis will start on the Mediums. 🟡 Lando and the two scarlet Ferraris on Hards.

And we think there could still be more rain on the way... 👀
The race will restart at 17:15. ⏰

Making the most of this red flag. 💪 

Switching out Lewis’ nose for a spare. 

Picked up heavy damage to his race wing battling Esteban. 💥💥 https://t.co/I0QS4W88AT
Red Flag.

VSC. Mick has had a big accident at the exit of the Swimming Pool. 

Good to see him climb out of that broken Haas. 🙏
This is good pace from GR. The fastest man on track and closing in on Charles for fourth. 👀

It's been a dramatic few laps - but George has jumped Lando in the stops. 💪

Lewis is the fastest man on track on these slicks - running P8.

Lewis boxes for the second time. He swaps his Inters for the hard slicks and is back out in P8.

All cars should be going to the end here unless we get any more drama... https://t.co/wxz7qSWCkG
And it's time! 💪 He's in for the slicks.

George is up to P5 and sticking with the wets!! 

Waiting for the perfect moment to make the move to the slicks. 👀 https://t.co/mxYMZyrT9g
Lewis is ALL over Esteban's Alpine here. 🦈

BOX. BOX. Lewis is in and makes the move onto the Inters! 

The crew send him on his way in 2.7s and he re-joins back in P9, behind Esteban.

Lewis telling us he's happy with these tyres. 🙏

Both of the boys are building a strong gap back to Esteban's Alpine in P9.

It's crucial to clear the pit stop window with overtaking so difficult here.

Everyone will be keeping an eye on Pierre's times.

He's P17 but the fastest man on track right now on the Inters.

George and Lewis maintain their positions in P6 and P8 in the opening laps. 💪

Lewis reports that the track is drying up pretty quickly. Timing the switch to the Inters will be key here. 👀 https://t.co/BSSedjVrC9
And we're RACING in Monaco!! 🫶
We are rolling once again in Monaco. Expecting two laps behind the Safety Car.
Let’s get this race started shall we, boys. 👊 https://t.co/mm6KtfvmN3

The news we’ve all been waiting for. 👏👏

The #MonacoGP will get started in 10 minutes time!
Hey boys. Keeping dry. 🙏 https://t.co/5IIRrBe3eG
https://t.co/sifwNcKfM7
Stop dancing. Stop dancing. 😂
Red Flag. The snake of cars return to the pitlane.

The field pulls away behind the @MercedesAMG Safety Car. 

These laps will count as formation laps. 

The rain is heavier than ever now. ☔️

Text:
Pushing on in these final laps - but George and Lewis struggling to make an impression into Checo's advantage in P2. 

Bring it home and bag those points, Team. 👊 https://t.co/2Kt9EJyipp
This typo. 🙃
George running nicely in P4 - 1.7s ahead of Lewis in the sister W13. Into the final 15 laps of the #AusGP. https://t.co/ul59apoDHE
VSC on lap 39/58: Max stops on track promoting George and Lewis into P3 and P4.

And Checo gets the move done on George in the faster Bull. 

The Silver Arrows running together in P4 and P5.

George gets a reminder on the radio that tyre management key today. 📻

Doing a fine job holding off Checo, but needs to take these Hards all the way to the end. 👀
George with his mirrors full of Bull. 😬 Checo tailing GR's W13 on lap 35. https://t.co/n4CS1Yk2mT
Lewis on the move. A slick pass down into Turn 1 and he's passed the Alpine and up into P5.

Lap 30/58 and still a long way to go in this race. George running P3 - ahead of Checo.

Lewis in P6 behind his old-friend Fernando. 👀
And then under attack from Fernando! 😬
George all over Max on that restart!! 😲😲

Lewis dives into the pits from P2 and re-joins in P5. A slick 2.8s by the boys in the garage!  

Warm up tricky on the new rubber though and he can't hold off Checo on his nicely warmed tyres.
The Silver Arrows move into P2 and P3 as the Bulls box for fresh rubber. 👊 https://t.co/qRCcDwtaDz

Lewis and George matching the pace of the Bulls now - both of the boys still focused on tyre management.

Treating these 🟡 Mediums as kindly as possible. https://t.co/0tcNQfT1Vo

Lewis leading a tight four-car pack including George, Lando and Daniel on lap 14 👊

Both our boys managing the Medium rubber with Max in P2 reporting struggles with front-left graining. https://t.co/8AdfSjcMWk

Lewis on the defence - with Checo closing in on that rapid looking Bull. 

The Mexican makes the move for P3 into Turn 3 with the help of DRS. 

Time to concentrate on our race with the McLarens now. 💪
Green again in Melbourne! Lewis and George both clean on the restart, running P3 and P5 on lap 7/58 👊 https://t.co/SrlZvGHCM4

Safety Car early in Melbourne with SAI’s scarlet Ferrari beached in the gravel. 

Just watching LH’s launch off the grid on the replays! 🔥🔥

Lewis up into P3 after that mega start, passing Lando and Checo! 

George moves into fifth and he’s got Lando’s McLaren as well!

LIGHTS OUT AT ALBERT PARK!! 

EXCELLENT START BY BOTH LEWIS AND GEORGE PICKING UP POSITIONS DOWN INTO TURN 1! https://t.co/nDiYme9Ddw

Formation lap is underway at Albert Park! 👊 

Let’s see your race predictions… 💭
F1 is BACK in Australia!! Drop your emoji flag and tell us where in the 🌏 you’re watching the #AusGP. 👇 https://t.co/Mw72FyReGu
@lxwisnorris @MercedesAMG @LewisHamilton @GeorgeRussell63 @amgmotorsport @PET_Motorsports 🙏 means a lot, thank you

Text: Still we rise, Team. Still we rise. 💪💛💜 #MondayMotivation https://t.co/gsZZ1m94kY

💬 "We certainly have our work cut out over the next weeks and months but we are more determined than ever to get ourselves back fighting at the front.”

Toto, Lewis, George and Shov debrief the #SaudiArabianGP 👇
We’re not going to stop pushing. 👊 https://t.co/1xM8GmmGFa
Not the race we were hoping for, but we’ll take our lessons from Jeddah and continue the work. 💪 https://t.co/W3IU29exrV

Under no illusions that we’re not where we should be right now in terms of performance.

But we can take heart from a solid 38 points from a tough opening two races.

And that’s credit to Lewis and George’s performances. 💪 https://t.co/VqyCQlIDiK

George and Lewis wrung absolutely everything they could out of the car tonight - with some great battles and overtakes. 👏

Unfortunately Lewis' race was compromised by the early Safety Car and we couldn't take advantage of the VSC to protect position. https://t.co/n0M7jAKsH9
The boys bring home double points after a tough race in Jeddah. 🙏 https://t.co/WjBs8nfYwY
Lewis passes Lance for P10 and is back into the points. Into the final laps tonight at Jeddah. https://t.co/wNZWPk1XNS
Lewis moves into P11. On a late charge. Keep pushing LH, the points still possible here.

VSC ends. LH dives in. And re-joins in P12 behind Kevin Magnussen.

Lewis on the Mediums with eight laps to go.
VSC called with RIC stopped at the entry to the pitlane. The pit entry is closed. Lewis Hamilton cannot pit...
📻 "Pace is still good. Keep this up." Bono happy with Lewis' lap times as he builds the gap back to Kevin. https://t.co/Sted2oejxj
Lewis going deep into this race on the Hards - P6 and still yet to stop as we hit lap 30/50. https://t.co/sVc86bWilS

A lap later and LH gets the move done into T1 with a lunge. 

The two Silver Arrows running P5 and  P6 as we hit lap 25.

Lewis and K-Mag swapping positions for P6. ⚔️

Lewis takes the position at the final corner, the Haas back past into P6.
Back racing in Jeddah. And George slices past Magnussen on the restart and moves into fifth! 🙌

An AMG is leading: 😁

It’s the Safety Car: 🙂

We have a Safety Car with a Williams in the wall.

George boxes and takes a new set of Hards and re-joins in P5, as Lewis moves into P7. https://t.co/wE84F2gL0g
George moves into P4 as Checo boxes from the lead.

Making steady progress. Lewis first clears Lando and then Pierre to move into P10.

K-Mag the car ahead - also on the Hards. 👀 https://t.co/XWrtwJ649q

This Alpine battle helping George stretch the gap back to P6. 💪

Lewis not enjoying the grip on these Hard tyres but he's up to P12 and closing in on the points. https://t.co/J86XN8Lx8P
George with a nice pass on Esteban to move into P5. 👊

A solid start from the boys, George covering off Alonso’s attacks to hold P5. 

Lewis crosses the line in P14 after that first lap. 👏
LIGHTS OUT IN JEDDAH!! https://t.co/u5o9uADVJC

George in P6 starts on the Medium rubber. 🟡

Lewis starts from 15th - one of just three cars on the Hards. ⚪️

The field pulls away on the formation lap. 

Lights out in Jeddah just minutes away… 👀
🌃🤩 https://t.co/6bdytUQxpB

Racing under the Jeddah lights tonight. 🌃🤩

Drop your emoji flag and tell us where you’re watching the race. 👇 https://t.co/On94rG75gu
